## ğŸ“Œ Project Overview

This project implements an **end-to-end Credit Card Fraud Detection system** using **Machine Learning** and deploys it as an interactive **Streamlit web application**.

The model is trained on a **highly imbalanced transactional dataset** and is designed to accurately identify fraudulent transactions while minimizing false negatives.  
After evaluating multiple algorithms, the **Extra Trees Classifier** was selected due to its strong performance on tabular data and robustness against imbalance.

---

## ğŸ¯ Objectives

- Detect fraudulent credit card transactions accurately  
- Handle highly imbalanced datasets effectively  
- Build a reliable and interpretable ML model  
- Deploy the trained model as a web application  
- Enable real-time fraud prediction for new transactions  

---

## ğŸ§  Machine Learning Approach

### âœ” Data Challenges
- Severe class imbalance (fraud cases are extremely rare)
- High-dimensional numerical features
- High cost of false negatives (missed frauds)

### âœ” Techniques Used
- **StandardScaler** for feature normalization  
- **SMOTE (Synthetic Minority Oversampling Technique)** to balance training data  
- **Extra Trees Classifier** for robust ensemble-based classification  
- Model evaluation using:
  - Recall (Primary Metric)
  - F1-Score
  - ROC-AUC
  - Confusion Matrix  

